00:00:41.542 --> 00:00:44.980
Now Tasker is basically a
device automation app.

00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:47.820
In the app clinic, they kind
of use the term profile,

00:00:47.820 --> 00:00:49.440
device profile apps.

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:52.240
This is kind of I guess
a subset of that.

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:55.200
Basically it lets you create
a system of constraints or

00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:58.880
contexts and create a set
of actions or tasks.

00:00:58.880 --> 00:01:03.730
I guess tasks are collections
of actions in this app that

00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:07.710
get run when the device
enters that kind of

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:09.130
profile, that context.

00:01:09.130 --> 00:01:15.080
So, for example, if the week day
is Monday through Friday

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:20.410
and the time of day is between
9:00 AM and 5:00 PM, you can

00:01:20.410 --> 00:01:24.290
be thought as in the
work profile or in

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:26.190
the work set of contexts.

00:01:26.190 --> 00:01:30.130
And then so once you enter that
context, rather enter

00:01:30.130 --> 00:01:31.930
that profile-- there's a lot
of terminology in this app.

00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:33.020
It's somewhat confusing.

00:01:33.020 --> 00:01:35.320
But it's very well
thought out.

00:01:35.320 --> 00:01:37.420
When you enter the context,
certain things can happen.

00:01:37.420 --> 00:01:39.930
When you leave that context
or profile,

00:01:39.930 --> 00:01:40.850
other things can happen.

00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:43.380
So there's an Enter
and Exit action.

00:01:43.380 --> 00:01:46.410
So that's at a very high level
what the app does.

00:01:46.410 --> 00:01:50.440
It lets you had to do a number
of different things from

00:01:50.440 --> 00:01:55.320
setting system settings
automatically, to speaking out

00:01:55.320 --> 00:01:59.310
text, to doing all sorts
of interesting things.

00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:02.160
And then of course, the number
of different profiles or

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:04.770
different constraints that they
have is also very large.

00:02:04.770 --> 00:02:07.030
So you can really, really
customize the set of

00:02:07.030 --> 00:02:08.330
behaviors you want.

00:02:08.330 --> 00:02:09.665
So this is the app.

00:02:09.665 --> 00:02:12.270
As you can see here, there's
kind of these three tabs--

00:02:12.270 --> 00:02:16.660
profiles, tasks, and scenes.

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:18.350
