00:15:15.280 --> 00:15:18.600
And surprisingly, one of the
things we see broken in a lot

00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:21.080
of them is touch feedback,
which is strange.

00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:23.880
Because it really does give
the user a sense of

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:27.860
responsiveness and indicate
that something's happening

00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:30.220
within the application.

00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:33.200
And the amount of effort
required to actually add good

00:15:33.200 --> 00:15:34.520
touch feedback in your
application is

00:15:34.520 --> 00:15:35.480
actually not that much.

00:15:35.480 --> 00:15:38.840
So it's definitely something
with lower amounts of effort

00:15:38.840 --> 00:15:40.950
that has great pay off.

00:15:40.950 --> 00:15:43.040
And of course the canonical
source for information on

00:15:43.040 --> 00:15:45.380
