00:16:03.960 --> 00:16:07.350
So the first thing to remember
is all interactive elements

00:16:07.350 --> 00:16:09.110
should provide feedback.

00:16:09.110 --> 00:16:11.350
Not some of them-- every single
one should provide some

00:16:11.350 --> 00:16:13.540
sort of feedback.

00:16:13.540 --> 00:16:16.180
ROMAN NURIK: They say if it does
something, it should look

00:16:16.180 --> 00:16:17.510
like it does something
when you press it.

00:16:17.510 --> 00:16:20.000
ADAM KOCH: Exactly.

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:22.610
And another point to make is
you should be consistent.

00:16:22.610 --> 00:16:26.170
So we often see people
customizing touch feedback for

00:16:26.170 --> 00:16:27.170
parts of the application.

00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:29.380
But then they don't go and
customize, say, the action bar

00:16:29.380 --> 00:16:30.560
touch feedback.

00:16:30.560 --> 00:16:32.780
So you have sort of the holo
blue in the action bar.

00:16:32.780 --> 00:16:34.640
But you have a completely
different color scheme for the

00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:37.890
rest of your application.

00:16:37.890 --> 00:16:39.630
ROMAN NURIK: And one that one
thing that can help with that

00:16:39.630 --> 00:16:45.280
is the Android holo colors
website, which basically

00:16:45.280 --> 00:16:47.420
generates all that for
developers, as well as the

00:16:47.420 --> 00:16:49.360
action bar style generator,
which again does all that for

00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:49.880
the [INAUDIBLE].

00:16:49.880 --> 00:16:50.070
ADAM KOCH: Yeah.

00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:52.330
Combining that will really
help you get sort of 99%

00:16:52.330 --> 00:16:56.500
through your application,
being consistent there.

00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:57.820
We'll touch on this
again in a second.

00:16:57.820 --> 00:17:00.380
But you should really ensure
that the full touchable target

00:17:00.380 --> 00:17:02.715
area has feedback, so not
just the portion of it.

00:17:02.715 --> 00:17:05.050
If it's touchable elsewhere, it
should really have feedback

00:17:05.050 --> 00:17:07.700
across the entire item.

00:17:07.700 --> 00:17:10.650
As we mentioned, customized ad
feedback for custom components

00:17:10.650 --> 00:17:11.540
and whatnot.

00:17:11.540 --> 00:17:13.800
